  "description": "You are the CRM administrator preparing for the end-of-quarter pipeline restructure. Execute the following directive from the VP of Sales. Login at http://localhost:8069 with admin / admin.\n\nInfrastructure:\n- Create a pipeline stage 'Negotiation' positioned between 'Proposition' and 'Won' with 75% default probability.\n- Create a sales team 'Strategic Accounts' with Mitchell Admin as team leader.\n- Create a lost reason 'Gone Dark - No Response'.\n\nProcess ALL opportunities in the pipeline according to these rules. Apply every matching rule to each opportunity:\n(a) Expected revenue >= $100,000: assign to 'Strategic Accounts' team, add tag 'Key Deal'.\n(b) Expected revenue >= $100,000 AND currently in 'Proposition' stage with probability >= 60%: additionally advance to 'Negotiation' stage.\n(c) Expected revenue < $50,000 AND in 'New' stage with probability <= 10%: mark as Lost with reason 'Gone Dark - No Response'.\n(d) Internal notes mention 'RivalSoft': add tag 'Competitive'.\n(e) Internal notes indicate the deal champion is leaving or departing: set priority to 3 stars (Urgent), add tag 'At Risk', and schedule a 'Call' activity for April 15, 2026 with summary 'Urgent: find new deal sponsor' assigned to Mitchell Admin.\n\nAfter all processing, tag every non-lost opportunity with 'Q1-Reviewed'.\n\nData cleanup:\n- Consolidate the duplicate company records for Caspian Technologies. The duplicate is named 'Caspian Tech'. Transfer all its opportunities to 'Caspian Technologies' and archive the duplicate.\n- For the 'Employee Portal Development' opportunity: rename it to 'Employee Portal - Phase 1', update expected revenue to $40,000 (the original quote mentioned in its internal notes), and log an internal note: 'Revenue and scope corrected per Q1 review.'",
  "difficulty": "very_hard",
  "init": {
    "timeout_sec": 2400,
    "max_steps": 400,
    "reward_type": "sparse"
  },
  "hooks": {
